definitions.definition: letters, numbers, or symbols that have been produced on paper by a machine using ink:
examples: The title is in bold print.
The debate is still raging, both in print and online.

definitions.definition: If a book is in print, it is possible to buy a new copy of it, and if it is out of print, it is not now possible:
examples: Is her work still in print?

definitions.definition: to produce writing or images on paper or other material with a machine:
examples: The leaflets will be printed on recycled paper.

definitions.definition: to include a piece of writing in a newspaper or magazine:
examples: Some newspapers still refuse to print certain swear words.

definitions.definition: to produce a newspaper, magazine, or book in large quantities:
examples: 20,000 copies of the novel will be printed in hardback.
